Bob.java: Add logic to create, write and append to tasks file
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, there was no logic to save the task list into a file in the
hard disk automatically.

Such logic will allow users to remember what they have previously input.

Let's,
* add the relevant logic to create the new directory and file if needed
* add a method to write to the file
* add a method to append text to the file

commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, there was no logic to support loading data from saved on the

to the chatbot previously.

Let's,
* add a method to add file contents into the current task list
* add a helper method to create tasks from the string inputs scanned
* add file contents to task list whenever data.txt file already exists

commitResults.messageTitle: Add assertions to code to if assumptions hold
commitResults.messageBody:
Several methods have implicit assumptions of specific properties in
parameters and variables.

It will be better to check if these assumptions hold, before moving on
to run the other parts of the code. This helps the debugging process
since the code will stop running at the point where one assumption made
does not hold true.

Add the ability to check and remove duplicates
commitResults.messageBody:
There is no restriction on what tasks can be added into the task list,
other than the input format specified.

This allows duplicate tasks, with the exact same details and
descriptions, to be added.

Let's
* add a command that allows users to check for duplicates
* add a command that allows users to remove all duplicates

commitResults.messageTitle: Handle all exceptions thrown
commitResults.messageBody:
Some exceptions thrown are not handled, which causes the program to
become unusable.

When exceptions are caught in the UI and error messages are returned as
text messages from Bob, users will have a better understanding of the
error that has occurred.

Let's update the methods in Bob.java and Ui.java to handle all
exceptions by returning the error messages as Strings.
